revised_title: Development and Structure of the Common Fowl's Skull
tldr: This study examines the development and structure of the skull in common fowls, from early embryonic stages to adulthood. The research focuses on the changes in the skeletal parts of the head and how they evolve throughout the bird's life. The findings contribute to a better understanding of the history and meaning of the Vertebrate skull in general.
scientific_discipline: Biology and Life Sciences > Vertebrate anatomy
